,Recommended,319480,20575355,"Posted: 16 January, 2016",all,jippalippa,"Odallus The Dark Call is the most faithful to the 8-bit era game ever made.Were many other fantastic games get close, like Hotline Miami, Shovel Knight, Axiom Verge, Broforce ecc...but can't achieve the real 8-bit look, Odallus triumphs, with its gorgeous visuals and its limited colour palette.It genuenly feels like playing with an old NES cartridge; the gameplay as well is perfectly faithful to the old classics.The game is very fun to play, with the classic platforming, combat and ""metroidvania-like"" exploring, but the best thing is that it even retains the classic little annoying control quirks that games such as castelvania 1,2,3 had. The controls are not very precise and you often receive hits you shouldn't, but that's the magic of the game because in the 80s/early 90s it was exactly like that!The game surely counts on the nostalgia of the player, but it's also the perfect title for a modern young player to start adventuring in the lovely world of retrogaming.The title, as expected, features a very inspired 8-bit look and the locations are even more astonishing; we have some constructions which remind us of the roman empire, mountains filled with snow and lava, very colourful forests, alien-like landscapes ecc...Even the difficulty is set on the 80s standards, very unforgiving with the lives and hard in general, but still not impossible (Boss battles are very schematic and ,with a bit of patience and learning of the patterns, can be beaten easily).Highly recommended to everybody, specially the nostalgic players like me who love to dive again in that lovely 1980s style of gaming."
