,Recommended,319480,17099390,"Posted: 17 July, 2015",all,Ringo,"TL;DR - If you like old school NES Castlevania then you'll like this.-Graphics are retro style and while it seems everybody is releasing games using them, they are a perfect fit for what is essentially NES Castlevania with a sword.-Controls: 4 direction movement, attack, jump, swap sub-item and menu. Up+Attack performs sub-item attack.-Combat is simple. Beat the♥♥♥♥♥♥out of stuff with your sword and sub-items until it dies. Enemies have patterns for movement and attacks with some randomization between them.-The upgrade system is direct and linear. Hold more sub-items, get stronger armor, stronger sword, more life.-There is a world map for selecting what stage you want to do. Stages are somewhat open with multiple paths to the stage boss as well as multiple exits which open different stages for you to select on the world map. You can revisit stages as often as you like and the world map gives you information about the stages regarding secrets found and whether you've killed the stage boss.-You have limited lives once you've started a stage but losing all your lives only kicks you back to the world map. You keep any upgrades you find along the way. You can also find merchants within the stages that will sell you food to restore life, more sub-item ammo and even extra lives.*Review posted with a little over an hour played and 4 stages completed."
