76561198041995956,Recommended,319480,18852420,"Posted: 2 November, 2015",all,bahamut66,"This company, Joymasher, seems to excel at NES style games.  This one is a superb mix of Castlevania, Metroid, and Astyanax.  It's got a dark story about gods abandoning the world and one man's quest to find his son and reclaim what little joy there is to be had in his life.  The sprites look great and the design work for the bosses is inspired with some horrific, sometimes even Lovecraftian nightmares staring you down.  Controls are tight and superb and the game has a plethora of secrets to find, with control schemes for classic NES controller, keyboard, or modern 360 controller.  It also does away with instant death traps and pits, for the most part, only taking a bit of health when you die...so in my opinion it's more polished than many old school NES games from way back when.  There are cut scenes and I wish we had more of them, but overall, there aren't too many flaws here.  If you want an old school NES game done right, with the polish and care of true pros, I say don't be dissuaded by this games price tag.  It's only 4-5 hours long if you really drag it out, but it's well worth the price of admission.  I had a great Halloween blowing through this game.Buy it."
