76561198173899526,Recommended,319480,32064030,Posted: 30 May,all,Groove Wizard,"Let's go straight to the point, this is your go-to castlevania-style game on Steam.Odallus clearly shines among the ridiculous number of attempts to recapture the spirit of good old NES games. There's an awesome catchy soundtrack all the way through, and the colorful design and choice of palette wonderfully manage to create this gloomy and yet badass atmosphere that is so typical of the Castlevania series.The gameplay itself is even more awesome, though, for there are a few features from modern platformers that make the character more maneuverable than fellow Richter Belmont, while the gameplay keeps the rigidity and tight controls we learnt to love in this kind of games.Difficulty-wise, it's what you should expect from a modern game that looks to feel like Castlevania. Normal mode might feel hard for those who are not that much into that kind of games, but it's still forgiving enough to not be a pain to beat.On the other hand, Veteran mode (NG+) is some serious♥♥♥♥♥♥ The game is cleverly reworked to be harder, but not in a repetitive way. You get to see new enemies, to go through a new route, for areas and item locations are different, bosses have new patterns, and running out of lives does matter. Basically one of the best NG+ I've ever seen.And did I mention the lore ? Oh come on, don't be shy, buy it !"
