,Recommended,319480,17151017,"Posted: 20 July, 2015",all,BONESNRUB,"A very solid action-platformer with a wealth of influences. Much like its contemporary, Shovel Knight, Odallus pays homage to some of the classics of the genre. Visually, it utilizes the best aesthetic sensibilities of NES-era titles like Castlevania to create something that is both atmospheric and complementary to the game's mechanics. It manages to feel authentic and evocative of the NES era without having to actually bend to that system's limitations.Where Shovel Knight was clearly influenced, mechanically, by games like Zelda 2, Ducktales, and Mega Man, Odallus feels more influenced by games like Castlevania, Super Metroid, and Demon's Crest. It even brings Dark Souls to mind, in the way the game spreads its checkpoints thin and punishes the player for being impatient.Odallus is a short game (my save file clocked in just shy of six hours), but never feels padded. I definitely feel like I got my $15 out of it. The difficulty hit a real sweet-spot for me, managing to be just punishing enough to keep me on my toes, and just fair enough in its difficulty to keep me engaged. It's not a technically flawless game (the way the camera snaps in certain levels can be jarring), I found the story to be virtually incomprehensible, and I encountered a few minor bugs, but nothing game-breaking. At the end of the day, I found Odallus to be a thoroughly satisfying game experience."
76561197995207287,Recommended,319480,17233700,"Posted: 26 July, 2015",all,Carl James,"This game is great.  Obviously not for everyone, but if you are in to retro inspired games that are clearly made with a lot of love and polish then this is for you.  Odallus is a sidescrolling action game with small bits of exploration to find all of the various power ups and one hidden boss.  Stages are chosen from an overworld map similar to Shovel Knight and allowing them to be tackled in the order of the users choosing while also having hidden exits to sub stages similar to Demon's Crest.  Combat consists of your standard sword attack and multiple sub weapons that the player can find or purchase from vendors throughout the game.  Clearly inspired by classics like the aforementioned Demon's Crest and Castlevania, but with it's own personality I would highly recommend this game."
