76561198062024294,Recommended,319480,17184580,"Posted: 23 July, 2015",all,Sith_1ord,"Odallus: The Dark Call is a Metroidvania-like platforming action game made in 8-bit style. In short the game is great. Gameplay, while having nothing really new, feels great. You have your normal sword which you find upgrdes for and three types of sub-weapons. There are no useless things in your inventory, you will find yourself using them at some point.The difficulty is decent: it offers a good challenge without becoming a nightmare to live through. What is nightmarish, though, is the enemy design: you can find many kinds of demonic creatures, some of which people might find disturbing. Overall design seems to be inspired by Berserk manga (it's so obvious that even I, who never read it, can see that) which adds more appeal for dark fantasy fans.UPD. Veteran Mode is out and boy it is hard. New difficulty setting provides an even better challenge, introducing new enemy types and changing power-up locations. However, they also added a lil' bit of fake difficulty: bosses now summon lesser enemies to assist them which often puts you in a situation when the damage cannot be avoided.I had great fun with this game, and frankly speaking, it's the best Castlevania-like games I played in recent time, deserving a solid 9/10.P.S. Omigod, this sequel hook!"
